The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Heat on MTV, V

 New Delhi, June 11 (PTI): The Centre has asked six cable television channels, including MTV and Channel V, to apologise for the telecast of objectionable videos or be ready to be pulled off air. 

 A hearing in person had been given to the authorities of the channels and after that it was decided that the channels should apologise on air, through a scroll, for three days beginning June 16, an official of the information and broadcasting ministry said. 

 Apart from these two music channels, others facing the heat are ITV, B4U, MH1 and etc. 

 In the scroll, they will have to say: The information and broadcasting ministry issues a warning to the music channel for violating programme code. This TV channel assures to be more careful in future. 




